cs.NA, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.MS, cs.CE 

The paper deals with uncertainty quantification and global sensitivity analysis for accelerator cavity design, which involves numerical simulations and modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.EM (Electromagnetism), as the paper deals with the Maxwell eigenvalue problem. The paper also involves system modeling and analysis, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control), and statistical analysis, which falls under cs.MS (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper reports on the manufacturing process of the cavities, which involves engineering and computational modeling, falling under cs.CE (Computational Engineering).
